# Client (React)

## Directory layout

```
client/src/
  api/           # HTTP clients, queryKeys.ts
  components/    # Shared UI (cross-feature)
  components/ui/ # Shadcn/Radix primitives (dialog, select, tooltip, …)
  features/[name]/
    components/
    hooks/
    lib/         # Feature-specific pure helpers
    tabs/
  hooks/         # App-wide hooks
  lib/           # Shared pure helpers (utils, badgeVariants, surfaceClasses)
  styles/        # Design tokens (tokens.css)
  types/         # Shared API/domain types
```

## Design tokens

Semantic colors and radii live in `src/styles/tokens.css` and are exposed to Tailwind via `@theme inline`.

| Token class | Use for |
|-------------|---------|
| `bg-background`, `text-foreground` | Page/surface base |
| `bg-card`, `text-card-foreground` | Cards, panels |
| `text-muted-foreground` | Secondary labels, hints |
| `border-border`, `border-input` | Borders, form controls |
| `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground` | Primary actions (brand purple) |
| `text-positive`, `text-negative`, `text-warning` | Market direction, sentiment |
| `bg-destructive`, `text-destructive` | Errors, delete actions |

- **Do** use semantic tokens (`text-foreground`, `border-border`) in new/changed UI.
- **Do not** add raw `slate-*`, `violet-*`, or hex colors in feature components — extend tokens in `tokens.css` if a new semantic is needed.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` when merging conditional classes.
- Reuse `PANEL_SHELL_CLASS` / `CARD_BASE_CLASS` from `@/lib/surfaceClasses` for shells (or use `Panel` / `Card`).

## Must

- **SoC:** components render UI only; hooks own state, effects, and data lifecycle; `api/` owns HTTP calls.
- **HTTP:** use the shared axios client (`@/api/client.ts`). No raw `fetch` in features, hooks, or components. (SSE via `EventSource` is the exception.)
- **API paths:** all API endpoints targeted by Axios must explicitly include the `/api/v1/` prefix (configured in the shared axios client base URL).
- **Paginated feeds:** when fetching lists from the server, always leverage `AsyncListPanel` or pass pagination parameters (`page`, `limit`). Do not request unbounded datasets from the API.
- **HTTP status checks** — compare against `HTTP_STATUS` from `@trading-signal/contracts/httpStatus`, not numeric literals.
- **Imports:** use `@/` path aliases (e.g. `@/components/Button`). No `../` chains across modules.
- **React Query:** cache keys in `@/api/queryKeys.ts` only.
- **Mutations:** no `onSuccess` on `useMutation` — call `mutateAsync`, then `invalidateQueries` in the hook wrapper (see `usePriceAlerts`).
- **Shared UI:** use components from `@/components/` instead of raw `<button>` / labeled `<input>` when a match exists.
- **Do not duplicate** panel shells, error banners, empty states, or badge markup — use the shared components below.
- **Primitives:** use `@/components/ui/*` for dialogs, dropdowns, tooltips, selects, skeletons. Use `@/components/Button` for app actions (do not import `@/components/ui/button` in features).
- **Overlays:** use `Dialog` from `@/components/ui/dialog` — no hand-rolled `fixed inset-0` modals.

## Component folder pattern

Each app component module:

```
Component/
  Component.tsx   # export default the component
  types.ts        # named type exports
  index.ts        # public barrel
```

Shadcn primitives live in `components/ui/*.tsx` (generated/owned; edit in place when needed). Optional `Component.module.css` only when Tailwind tokens are not sufficient.

`index.ts` barrel:

```ts
export { default } from './Component'
export { default as Component } from './Component'
export type { ComponentProps } from './types'
```

## Component file layout (`.tsx`)

Follow this **top-to-bottom order** in every component module. Shared/exported types belong in sibling `types.ts` (layer 2 applies to **file-local** types only).

| # | Section | What goes here |
|---|---------|----------------|
| 1 | **Imports** | External packages, then `@/` aliases, then relative imports. Type-only imports use `import type`. |
| 2 | **Types & interfaces** | File-local types only. Promote to `types.ts` when exported or reused. |
| 3 | **Small helper components** | Private sub-components used only in this file (e.g. row, header). |
| 4 | **Main component** | The exported (default) component function. |
| 5 | **Hooks** | First statements inside the main component — `useState`, `useEffect`, custom hooks, React Query. |
| 6 | **Guard clauses** | Early returns: loading, error, empty, missing props. |
| 7 | **Render** | Final `return (...)` with JSX. |

**Inside the main component:** hooks → derived values/handlers → guard clauses → render. Do not interleave hooks with conditional logic (`react-hooks/rules-of-hooks`).

```tsx
// 1. Imports
import { useState } from 'react'
import { EmptyState } from '@/components/EmptyState'
import { LoadingSpinner } from '@/components/LoadingSpinner'
import type { WidgetProps } from './types'

// 2. Types (file-local)
type WidgetView = 'loading' | 'ready'

// 3. Helper components
function WidgetHeader({ title }: { title: string }) {
  return <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground">{title}</h3>
}

// 4–7. Main component
function Widget({ title, items, isLoading }: WidgetProps) {
  // 5. Hooks
  const [view, setView] = useState<WidgetView>('loading')

  // 5b. Handlers / derived state (after hooks, before guards)
  const hasItems = items.length > 0

  // 6. Guard clauses
  if (isLoading) {
    return <LoadingSpinner label="Loading widget…" />
  }

  if (!hasItems) {
    return <EmptyState message="No items yet." />
  }

  // 7. Render
  return (
    <section>
      <WidgetHeader title={title} />
      <ul>{items.map((item) => <li key={item.id}>{item.label}</li>)}</ul>
    </section>
  )
}

export default Widget
```

### ESLint

| Layer | Enforced today | Notes |
|-------|----------------|-------|
| Hooks before guards/render | Yes | `eslint-plugin-react-hooks` (`rules-of-hooks`, `exhaustive-deps`) |
| Import order | Yes | `eslint-plugin-perfectionist` — external → `@/` → relative; `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` |
| Types in `types.ts` | Review / rules | Promote shared types; do not rely on ESLint alone |
| Helpers → main → guards → render | No | Convention for readability; no standard ESLint rule covers full file layout |

Pure helpers (no JSX) belong in feature `lib/*Utils.ts`, not in the component file.

## Shadcn primitives (`@/components/ui/`)

| Component | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `dialog` | Modals, confirmations, create forms |
| `dropdown-menu` | Row actions, overflow menus |
| `tooltip` | Hints on weights, icons (app wrapped in `TooltipProvider` in `main.tsx`) |
| `select` | Single-choice pickers (chart range, enums) |
| `skeleton` | Loading placeholders |

Add more with `npx shadcn@latest add <name> -c client` from the repo root.

## App shared components (`@/components/`)

| Component | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `Button` | All clickable actions (`primary`, `secondary`, `danger`, `tab`, `tabActive`) |
| `FormField` | Labeled text/number inputs |
| `CheckboxField` | Boolean options (e.g. email alerts) |
| `StatusCard` | API health display |
| `Toast` / `ToastProvider` | Notifications (wired in `main.tsx`) |
| `Badge` | Status/label pills — use `variant` from `@/lib/badgeVariants` via domain helpers |
| `Panel` | Titled section shells (`section`, `feed`, `page` variants) |
| `Card` | Bordered content surfaces (`default`, `muted`, `interactive`, `selected`, `highlight`, `unread`) |
| `EmptyState` | No-data placeholders |
| `ErrorMessage` | Inline API/validation error banners |
| `LoadingSpinner` | Inline loading indicator with label |
| `AsyncListPanel` | Feed/list panels with loading, error, empty, and item render props |

## Shared lib helpers

| Module | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `@/lib/utils` | `cn()` — merge Tailwind classes |
| `@/lib/surfaceClasses` | `PANEL_SHELL_CLASS`, `CARD_BASE_CLASS` |
| `@/lib/badgeVariants` | `BadgeVariant`, `badgeClassName()` |
| `@/lib/formatDate` | `formatPublishedAt()` and other date display |
| `@/lib/signalUtils` | Watchlist signal actions, change % formatting |
| Feature `*Utils.ts` | Domain-specific badge variant mappers (e.g. `sentimentBadgeVariant`) |

Map domain values to `BadgeVariant` in feature utils; render with `<Badge variant={...}>` — do not copy Tailwind badge classes.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ fetch in component
useEffect(() => { fetch('/api/v1/price-alerts').then(...) }, [])

// ✅ api module + hook
import { api } from '@/api/client'
const { alerts, createAlert } = usePriceAlerts()
```

```tsx
// ❌ duplicated panel markup
<section className="rounded-2xl border ...">
  <header>...</header>
</section>

// ✅ shared Panel
import { Panel } from '@/components/Panel'
<Panel title="Price alerts" description="..." variant="section">...</Panel>
```

```tsx
// ❌ inline error styles
<p className="rounded-lg border border-red-200 bg-red-50 ...">{error}</p>

// ✅ ErrorMessage
import { ErrorMessage } from '@/components/ErrorMessage'
<ErrorMessage message={error} />
```

```tsx
// ❌ raw badge spans with duplicated classes
<span className="rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-emerald-100 ...">

// ✅ Badge + domain variant helper
import { Badge } from '@/components/Badge'
import { signalActionBadgeVariant } from '@/lib/signalUtils'
<Badge variant={signalActionBadgeVariant(action)}>{action}</Badge>
```

```tsx
// ❌ deep relative import
import { Button } from '../../../../components/Button'

// ✅ path alias
import { Button } from '@/components/Button'
```

```tsx
// ❌ inline type in component file
type FormState = { symbol: string }

// ✅ features/alerts/types.ts (or narrower sibling types.ts)
export type PriceAlertFormState = { symbol: string }
```

```tsx
// ❌ hand-rolled modal overlay
{open ? <div className="fixed inset-0 z-50 ...">...</div> : null}

// ✅ Dialog
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle } from '@/components/ui/dialog'
<Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>...</Dialog>
```

```tsx
// ❌ raw slate colors
<p className="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Hint</p>

// ✅ semantic token
<p className="text-muted-foreground">Hint</p>
```

## Prefer

- Short JSDoc on every function/component/hook.
- Feature `lib/*Utils.ts` for pure formatting/validation logic.
- `AsyncListPanel` for tab feeds that load a list with loading/error/empty states.
- Extract to `@/components/` when the same UI pattern appears **3+ times**.

## Avoid

- Copy-pasting panel shells — use `Panel` or `PANEL_SHELL_CLASS`.
- Raw `slate-*` / `violet-*` / hex in feature UI — use design tokens.
- Hand-rolled modals, dropdowns, or tooltips — use `@/components/ui/*`.
- New one-off spinner/error/empty markup in feature components.
- Domain-specific badge Tailwind in feature components — map to `BadgeVariant` instead.
- Importing `@/components/ui/button` in features — use `@/components/Button`.
